9-9-9-21t9-21q9-9 21-9t21 9l278 278q5 5 7 10t2 11q0 6-2 11t-7 10L501-181q-9 9-21 9t-21-9q-9-9-9-21t9-21l227-227Z\"/></svg>                    </i>\n                </a>\n            </h3>\n            <p class=\"text-sm  md:text-md  sr-only  sm:not-sr-only  sm:line-clamp-2  md:line-clamp-3  text-main/70  mb-4xs\">UpdraftPlus now supports MEGA as an S3-compatible backup storage option. Discover what this means and why MEGA is a great new choice.</p>\n            <time class=\"absolute  bottom-sm  text-xs  md:text-sm  font-800\" datetime=\"2025-07-11\">11 Jul 2025</time>\n        </div>\n    </article>\n</li>                </ul>\n            </div>\n                    </div>\n    </div>\n\n</section><p>The post <a href=\"https://teamupdraft.com/blog/wp-optimize-release-v4-0-0/\">WP-Optimize release v4.0.0</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://teamupdraft.com\">TeamUpdraft</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n					\n										\n					\n		\n		\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"WP-Optimize release v3.8.0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:56:\"https://teamupdraft.com/blog/wp-optimize-release-v3-8-0/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 19 Dec 2024 16:51:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Company news\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Releases\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"WP-Optimize\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:33:\"https://teamupdraft.com/?p=297451\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:375:\"<p>This update brings exciting new premium features, including the ability to track 404 errors on your WordPress website. Learn how to enhance your site\'s performance and user experience.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://teamupdraft.com/blog/wp-optimize-release-v3-8-0/\">WP-Optimize release v3.8.0</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://teamupdraft.com\">TeamUpdraft</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"TeamUpdraft\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46108:\"<section data-layout=\"article\" class=\"bg-white\">\n    <div class=\"container  py-rg\">\n        <div class=\"grid  gap-sm  grid-cols-1  sm:grid-cols-2  md:grid-cols-3  lg:grid-cols-4  xl:grid-cols-5  relative\">\n            \n            <!-- 1st column -->\n            <div class=\"hidden  xl:block  xl:col-end-s1\"></div>\n\n            <!-- Main collumn -->\n            <div class=\"col-end-s1  sm:col-end-s2  lg:col-end-s3\">\n\n                <div class=\"toc-start\"></div>\n\n                <div class=\"wysiwyg\">\n\n                    \n<p>This update introduces major new premium features. The latest release allows you to see where users are seeing 404 errors on your WordPress website. It also includes improvements to the â€˜unused image detectionâ€™ feature. Weâ€™ve also introduced a new system status page to both the free and premium versions of the plugin. And weâ€™ve rolled out key fixes for cache and database functionality, as well as some usability improvements.</p>\n\n<h2>New system status page (free and premium)</h2>\n<p>The new system status page shows general details about your siteâ€™s health and includes a WP-Optimize section with info like your current plugin version and settings.</p>\n<p>This feature helps our support team assist you faster by listing important details about your siteâ€™s setup in one place. You can find the system status page under the settings &gt; system status on the WP-Optimize dashboard.</p>\n\n<!-- image -->\r\n<figure data-layout=\"image\" class=\"overflow-hidden  rounded-md\" data-alt=\"Screenshot of the System Status page in WP-Optimize settings, displaying key performance data and configuration details.\">\r\n    <img decoding=\"async\"\r\n                class=\"bg-main-1/3  border  border-main-1/10\"\r\n                loading=\"lazy\"\r\n        alt=\"Screenshot of the System Status page in WP-Optimize settings, displaying key performance data and configuration details.\"\r\n        width=\"1888\"\r\n        height=\"699\"\r\n        src=\"https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/wp-optimize-system-status-page-640x237.png\"\r\n        srcset=\"https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/wp-optimize-system-status-page-640x237.png 640w, https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/wp-optimize-system-status-page-1024x379.png 1024w, https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/wp-optimize-system-status-page-1440x533.png 1440w, https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/wp-optimize-system-status-page-300x111.png 300w, https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/wp-optimize-system-status-page-1280x474.png 1280w, https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/wp-optimize-system-status-page-768x284.png 768w, https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/wp-optimize-system-status-page-1680x622.png 1680w, https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/wp-optimize-system-status-page-600x222.png 600w, https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/wp-optimize-system-status-page.png 1888w\"\r\n        sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\"\r\n    >\r\n    </figure>\r\n<!-- image -->\n\n<h2>Log recurrent 404 requests (exclusive to premium users)</h2>\n<p>WP-Optimize now logs recurrent 404 requests, helping you identify broken links and take action to resolve them. The logs can be found under theÂ <strong>performance tabÂ </strong>in the WP-Optimize dashboard.</p>\n<h2>Improvements to unused image detection (exclusive to premium users)</h2>\n<p>For premium users, weâ€™ve improved the â€˜unused image detectionâ€™ feature. It can now detect unused images that are stored outside of the media library.</p>\n<h2>Fixes for cache and database functionality</h2>\n<p>This update includes several fixes to both free and premium versions to address issues reported by users:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Legacy widgets visibility: resolved an issue where legacy widgets were not displaying correctly when the WP-Optimize cache was enabled.</li>\n<li>UI issue with preload cancellation: fixed a bug where the preload â€œcancelâ€ option disappeared after instantly reloading the settings page.</li>\n<li>Database optimisation status: corrected a problem where optimising a single database item unintentionally changed the status of other items.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Improvements to logging, warnings, and usability</h2>\n<p>Weâ€™ve made several tweaks and refinements to both free and premium versions to improve usability and performance:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Cache purge logging:</strong>Â weâ€™ve added logging for cache purge operations, which can now be found under <strong>uploads/wpo/logs/cache-*.log.</strong> These logs will help you keep track of purge events, identify performance issues, and quickly debug any issues.</li>\n<li><strong>Warning messages: </strong>weâ€™ve added a confirmation warning before deleting post metadata or orphaned relationship data to help prevent accidental loss.</li>\n<li><strong>CRON overdue guide:</strong>Â the CRON overdue guide now opens in a new tab for easier reference.</li>\n<li><strong>Persistent analytics tab:</strong>Â the analytics tab will remain visible even when minification is disabled.</li>\n<li><strong>Improved UI: </strong>weâ€™ve added more info to our Google Analytics pages to make them easier to navigate.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>For a full list of changes, please review the changelog below.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Feature:</strong> Added a system status page</li>\n<li><strong>Feature:</strong> Logs frequent and highly recurrent 404 requests; introduces a new performance tab.</li>\n<li><strong>Fix:</strong> Cache â€“ Legacy Widgets visibility issue with WP-Optimize Cache enabled</li>\n<li><strong>Fix:</strong> Cache â€“ UI issue: Preload â€œCancelâ€ option is gone after reloading the WPO settings page instantly</li>\n<li><strong>Fix:</strong> Database â€“ optimizing any item also changes the status of other items</li>\n<li><strong>Refactor:</strong> Minify â€“ Removal of the <code>WPO_MINIFY_PHP_VERSION_MET</code> constant</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak:</strong> Add a warning message before deleting post metadata or orphaned relationship data.</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak:</strong> Bailout early if the minimum PHP version is not met</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak:</strong> Introduced logging for cache purge operations, available under <strong>uploads/wpo/logs/cache-*.log</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Tweak:</strong> Open CRON overdue guide in new tab</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak:</strong> Persist Analytics Tab when minification is disabled</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak:</strong> Premium â€“ Unused Images â€“ Improved detection of images not present in the Media Library, marking them as used</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak:</strong> UI improvements in Analytics section</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak:</strong> Wrapped checkboxes inside label tags in the confirmation popup that appears when clicking the <strong>â€œRemoveâ€ button</strong> on the <strong>Database &gt; Tables tab</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n                </div>\n\n                <!-- Author -->\n                <div class=\"mt-rg\">\n                    <h3 class=\"mb-xs\">About the author</h3>\n                    <div class=\"col-end-s5  flex\">\n                        <div>\n                            <div class=\"block  bg-white  border-3  border-orange  mr-xs  overflow-hidden  rounded-full  relative  size-[70px]\">\n                                <figure class=\"block  absolute  inset-[3px]  rounded-full  overflow-hidden\">\n                                                                        <img decoding=\"async\"\n                                        class=\"absolute  inset-0  m-auto  object-cover  h-full  w-full\"\n                                        loading=\"lazy\" \n                                        alt=\"Team Updraft Logo with dark background\"\n                                        width=\"150\"\n                                        height=\"150\"\n                                        src=\"https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/teamupdraft-author-bio-image.webp\"\n                                    >\n                                                                    </figure>\n                            </div>\n                        </div>\n                        <div>\n                            <h4 class=\"block  text-rg  my-4xs  font-800\">TeamUpdraft</h4>\n                            <p class=\"font-400  text-sm  my-0\">Our team consists of WordPress developers, marketers, and industry experts committed to provi